{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "4b41b0d0-6b5c-4a45-8a16-0e88e8d9c1d0",
    "name": "LIQUERA API",
    "description": "Collection (v2.1) alinhada com as rotas em `src/app.ts` e `src/routes/**`.\n\nAuth:\n- `Authorization: Bearer <JWT>` (login) OU `Authorization: Bearer <API_KEY>` (prefixo `lk_`) nas rotas híbridas.\n- Admin: `Authorization: Bearer <JWT role=ADMIN>`.\n\nVariáveis principais:\n- baseUrl (ex: http://localhost:80)\n- userEmail/userPassword, adminEmail/adminPassword\n- token/adminToken/authToken\n- merchantId/apiKey/apiKeyId/chargeId/txid/infractionId/webhookId\n- transfeeraWebhookSecret (opcional; se vazio, /v1/webhooks/transfeera aceita sem assinatura).\n\nWebhooks multi-endpoint:\n- Cada merchant pode ter N webhooks, cada um inscrito em eventos específicos.\n- GET /v1/webhooks/merchant/events para ver eventos disponíveis.\n- POST /v1/webhooks/merchant cria webhook com url, name e events.\n- PATCH /v1/webhooks/merchant/:id atualiza webhook.\n- DELETE /v1/webhooks/merchant/:id remove webhook.\n- events=[] é wildcard (recebe todos os eventos).\n\nInfrações PIX (MED):\n- Webhook Transfeera envia evento `Infraction` → salvo no banco\n- Merchant analisa: POST /v1/merchants/me/infractions/:id/analyze → AWAITING_APPROVAL\n- Admin aprova e envia ao adquirente: POST /v1/admin/infractions/:id/approve\n- Admin pode sincronizar via: POST /v1/admin/infractions/sync",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
